      <block class="full_text">
        <p>LEAD: To the Editor:</p>
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Vivian Gornick says she thinks Raymond Carver ''yearns to believe that [life]  should have been good, not that it actually was.''</p>
        <p>I disagree. From Carver's work I receive the sense of yearning for what was, of trying to think about love and its loss and even its recapture. I think he believed life was good. And he passed it on to us.</p>
        <p>JIM WEIKART</p>
        <p>New York</p>
      </block>
